f this collaboration included the world’s largest led lighting installation to date  branches have been retrofitted with led lighting helping to cut chase’s lighting energy consumption by  percent or the equivalent of taking nearly  cars off the road jpmorgan chase is on target to reach its goal to reduce greenhouse gas emissions  percent below  levels by  and continues to offset  percent of emissions generated by employee air travel on an annual basis in addition to the new solar pilot the company promotes renewable energy by supporting projects that bring new renewable energy capacity to the grid view text version read more about the collaboration between jpmorgan chase and current powered by ge ﻿ related stories related stories click to hide the content below click to show the content below technology connects ideas and colleagues across the globe jpmorgan chase global technology innovation week where technology meets big ideas read more about technology connects ideas and colleagues across the globe chase and current powered by ge collaborate to cut energy use in branches across the us jpmorgan chase has entered the second phase of an ongoing collaboration with current powered by ge to install new energy management and digital technologies read more about chase and current powered by ge collaborate to cut energy use in branches across the us what can high school students learn from jamie dimon a qa session with the fellowship initiative los angeles read more about what can high school students learn from jamie dimon the sun breaks through thoughts from a tfi fellow moving past tragedy and toward hope read more about the sun breaks through thoughts from a tfi fellow a second family how a tfi fellow finds greatness within a young man builds a new support network to succeed read more about a second family how a tfi fellow finds greatness within how four bankers helped launch a chicago nonprofit jpmorgan chase service corps program uses employee expertise to support